     Sidecar Pause-Detection & Load Balancer Drain Support

     Context

     The load balancer currently routes requests via round-robin with no awareness of server health beyond connection failures. When
     servers pause (GC, GIL, etc.), requests pile up in OS queues causing cascading latency. The sidecar process detects these pauses
     and tells the LB to stop routing traffic via DRAIN/RESUME commands over TCP.

     Part 1: Load Balancer Modifications

     1.1 lb/src/drain_manager.ts (NEW)

     - DrainManager class with per-server drain state tracking via Map<string, DrainState>
     - drain(server, durationMs): sets drained=true, starts auto-resume timer, clears previous timer
     - resume(server): sets drained=false, clears timer
     - isDrained(server): returns boolean
     - shutdown(): clears all timers
     - Key format: "host:port"

     1.2 lb/src/sidecar_listener.ts (NEW)

     - SidecarListener class — creates a net.Server for each server that has a sidecarPort
     - Accepts TCP connections, parses newline-delimited messages
     - Handles DRAIN:<duration_ms> → calls drainManager.drain()
     - Handles RESUME → calls drainManager.resume()
     - Buffer accumulation for partial reads, split on \n
     - start() / stop() lifecycle methods

     1.3 lb/src/router.ts (MODIFY)

     - Constructor accepts optional DrainManager
     - next() return type: ServerConfig | null
     - Tries up to servers.length positions, skipping drained servers
     - Returns null when all servers drained (index still advances for fairness)

     1.4 lb/src/proxy_server.ts (MODIFY)

     - handleRequest: if router.next() returns null, respond 503 Service Unavailable

     1.5 lb/src/main.ts (MODIFY)

     - Create DrainManager, pass to RoundRobinRouter
     - Create SidecarListener, start/stop alongside proxy server

     1.6 lb/src/index.ts (MODIFY)

     - Add re-exports for DrainManager, SidecarListener

     1.7 Tests

     - lb/src/__tests__/drain_manager.test.ts — drain/resume, auto-resume timer, re-drain resets timer
     - lb/src/__tests__/sidecar_listener.test.ts — TCP integration test with mock client
     - Update lb/src/__tests__/router.test.ts — skip drained servers, null when all drained
     - Update lb/src/__tests__/proxy_server.test.ts — 503 when no servers available

